'''Choralography''' is a term that started as a joke, and has slowly become used so often that people forget it used to be funny. A compound word made from [[chorus]] or [[choral]] and [[choreography]], '''choralography''' refers to choreography performed by a chorus while singing. It may be as simple as having all the chorus members sway together or wave their arms, or it may involve complex rhythms and movement, or in extremely fabulous examples, quick costume changes.